.SS "loadMapData (BinaryString data, int mapWidth = \fR0\fP, int mapHeight = \fR0\fP, int dstX, int dstY)"

.PP
Load tile data from a binary string into the specified region of the layer\&. This function loads tile data from a BinaryString into a specific rectangular region of the \fBTileLayer\fP\&. The data is interpreted as a 2D array of tile indices\&.

.PP
\fBParameters\fP
.RS 4
\fIdata\fP The BinaryString containing the tile data to load 
.br
\fImapWidth\fP The width of the tile map in the data (number of tiles horizontally) 
.br
\fImapHeight\fP The height of the tile map in the data (number of tiles vertically) 
.br
\fIdstX\fP The X coordinate where to place the top-left corner of the loaded data in the layer 
.br
\fIdstY\fP The Y coordinate where to place the top-left corner of the loaded data in the layer
.RE
.PP
The BinaryString data should contain tile indices arranged in row-major order (left to right, top to bottom)\&. Each tile index corresponds to a tile in the \fBTileLayer\fP's tile set\&.

.PP
The function will load the specified rectangular region from the data into the layer starting at the destination coordinates (dstX, dstY)\&.

.PP
\fBWarning\fP
.RS 4
The function will overwrite existing tile data in the destination region 

.PP
If the data size doesn't match mapWidth * mapHeight, the behavior is undefined 
.RE
.PP
\fBNote\fP
.RS 4
Tile indices in the data should be valid for the layer's tile set
.RE
.PP
\fBSee also\fP
.RS 4
\fBTileLayer::loadMapData(MemBlock, int, int, int, int)\fP 

.PP
\fBTileLayer::getMapData()\fP 

.PP
BinaryString 
.RE
.PP

